-- Bank of Finland Promotes Poesoe to Head General Secretariat
-- B y   K a s p e r   V i i t a
-- 2012-06-19T13:51:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-19/bank-of-finland-promotes-poesoe-to-head-general-secretariat.html
Bank of Finland promoted Mika Poesoe
to become head of the general secretariat.  Poesoe, who’s head of communications, will succeed Antti Suvanto on Sept. 1, according to a  statement  by the Helsinki-
based central bank.  Suvanto will become an adviser to the bank’s three-member
board, led by  Erkki Liikanen , its governor and a member of the
European Central Bank council.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kasper Viita in Helsinki at 
